article.headline: Samford 65, Southeast Missouri State 64
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Jerry Smith made a layup with 2 seconds left Tuesday to give Samford a 65-64 win over Southeast Missouri State. The game-winning shot came after Roderick Pearson hit a layup to give Southeast Missouri a one-point lead with 7 seconds remaining. Smith, who led all players with 24 points, took the inbounds pass end-to-end for the final basket. The Redhawks (3-9, 1-4 Ohio Valley Conference) led 29-25 at the half, but had problems with Samford's inside game. The Bulldogs (4-4, 2-0) went on a 12-4 run late in the second half to take a 61-55 lead, then didn't trail again until Pearson's layup gave Southeast Missouri a 64-63 advantage. Pearson led the Redhawks with 18 points, Terrick Willoughby scored 12 and Michael Rembert added 11. Randall Gulina, the OVC's leading scorer, had 21 points for Samford and Travis Peterson added 10.
